30:11.363 --> 30:13.033
Yes, I am.

30:13.033 --> 30:15.363
\hHey, we’re having, like,
a nice Thanksgiving dinner.

30:15.363 --> 30:17.132
Maybe we just leave
\h\h\hHannah alone.

30:17.132 --> 30:18.660
How old are you?

30:18.660 --> 30:19.924
\h\h\hWhat?
(scoffs)

30:19.924 --> 30:21.660
So--

30:21.660 --> 30:23.264
19 1/2.

30:23.264 --> 30:25.957
You know, the last time
\h\hI made a "donation"

30:25.957 --> 30:28.099
was 22 years ago.

30:28.099 --> 30:30.297
22.

30:30.297 --> 30:33.759
Never had a client named Bloom,
and I remember all my clients.

30:33.759 --> 30:35.165
And I cared about each
and every one of them,

30:35.165 --> 30:36.495
and I’m not gonna let you

30:36.495 --> 30:38.792
ruin my daughter’s
\h\h\hThanksgiving.

30:38.792 --> 30:41.858
ROXY:
Wait, you’re not a-a...

30:41.858 --> 30:42.891
<i>(tense music)</i>

30:42.891 --> 30:44.198
HANNAH:
I can’t believe

30:44.198 --> 30:45.627
I’m being called out
by the dude

30:45.627 --> 30:48.330
who illegally inseminated
a bunch of women.

30:48.330 --> 30:50.165
I mean, that’s super fair.

30:50.165 --> 30:51.693
(chuckles)
Not.

30:51.693 --> 30:54.231
Hannah, I think it’s maybe time
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hyou leave.

30:54.231 --> 30:56.297
Sure.

30:56.297 --> 30:59.726
But it’s ’cause I’m telling
\h\h\h\h\hthe truth, right?

30:59.726 --> 31:01.693
\h\hYou all know it.
You’re only together

31:01.693 --> 31:04.396
\hbecause of a lie
that this guy told.

31:04.396 --> 31:06.330
\h\h\h\h\hAnd I’m the one
that’s being called out?

31:06.330 --> 31:09.000
Hey, okay, that’s enough.
You can go now.

31:09.000 --> 31:10.693
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hYou should talk.
You’re the biggest liar of all.

31:10.693 --> 31:12.330
Hey! No.

31:12.330 --> 31:13.660
\h\hDon’t do that.
Don’t go after her.

31:13.660 --> 31:15.594
Edie, what is this girl
talking about?

31:15.594 --> 31:17.759
Nothing. Please don’t talk
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\habout my wife,

31:17.759 --> 31:20.231
\h\h\h\h\h\hbecause you don’t know
what the hell you’re saying.

31:20.231 --> 31:21.759
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hCome on, Roxy,
let’s get out of here.

31:21.759 --> 31:23.231
We don’t need this.

31:23.231 --> 31:24.726
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:24.726 --> 31:26.000
I’m not going with you.

31:26.000 --> 31:27.825
You tricked me.

31:27.825 --> 31:29.825
\hBut I just wanted
to be your friend.

31:29.825 --> 31:31.495
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:31.495 --> 31:34.264
Wha--how else was I suppose
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hto do that?

31:34.264 --> 31:36.396
You--you would have never
responded to my messages.

31:36.396 --> 31:39.099
Get the hell out, now!

31:39.099 --> 31:40.528
Fine.

31:40.528 --> 31:42.726
\h\h\h\hJust so you know,
you made it way too easy.

31:42.726 --> 31:44.066
Excuse me?

31:44.066 --> 31:46.726
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hJULIA:
Don’t listen to her, Roxy.

31:46.726 --> 31:48.396
All I had to do was
compliment you,

31:48.396 --> 31:50.594
and you just rolled over
like a puppy.

31:50.594 --> 31:53.297
You’re no better
than anyone else on Insta,

31:53.297 --> 31:55.099
still acting like
you’re a big deal,

31:55.099 --> 31:58.066
when IRL, you’re just tragic.

31:58.066 --> 32:00.528
-What’s IRL?
-Mom, later.

32:02.033 --> 32:04.264
Hey, it’s okay.
\h\hCome here.

32:04.264 --> 32:07.099
Excuse me.
\h\h\hUh...

32:07.099 --> 32:08.627
I’m not feeling very well.

32:08.627 --> 32:10.594
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h(softly)
I think I need to be alone.

32:10.594 --> 32:11.924
Just wait.
\h\hHold on.

32:11.924 --> 32:14.429
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hCan I have
one minute alone, please,

32:14.429 --> 32:16.594
where everybody is not
\h\h\h\hup in my grill?

32:16.594 --> 32:19.858
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:19.858 --> 32:22.759
(door slams)

32:22.759 --> 32:25.330
DONOVAN: Uh...
(clears throat) Hey. Hi.

32:25.330 --> 32:26.462
\h\h\h\h-Oh, my God.
-Sorry to interrupt.

32:26.462 --> 32:28.396
The door was open.

32:28.396 --> 32:30.924
(chuckles)
Happy Thanksgiving.

32:30.924 --> 32:34.627
Ah, Donovan, this is everyone.
\h\hEveryone, this is Donovan.

32:34.627 --> 32:37.132
It’s about time.

32:37.132 --> 32:39.561
Let’s carve the damn turkey.

32:40.759 --> 32:42.891
-I’m so sorry. I, uh...
\h\h\h\h\h\h-It’s okay.

32:47.297 --> 32:48.561
I’m so sorry I’m late.

32:48.561 --> 32:50.099
My phone died,
and then my car died.

32:50.099 --> 32:52.561
Oh, your--your phone died.
His phone died.

32:52.561 --> 32:54.330
Yeah, so I took the ferry,
but I didn’t have my Dramamine.

32:54.330 --> 32:55.660
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h-Oh.
-So that was interesting.

32:55.660 --> 32:57.132
And then I couldn’t find
a taxi,

32:57.132 --> 32:58.462
-because...Thanksgiving.
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h-Right.

32:58.462 --> 33:00.693
And so I just had to walk,
and I’m sorry.

33:00.693 --> 33:03.198
(chuckles) It’s perfectly okay.
\h\hWe’re gonna get through this.

33:04.297 --> 33:05.792
Hi, sorry I’m late, everybody.

33:05.792 --> 33:09.033
Uh, it’s really nice
to meet you, Mr. Bechley.

33:09.033 --> 33:10.594
-It’s Dr. Bechley.
\h\h\h-DONOVAN: Oh.

33:10.594 --> 33:11.924
I wasn’t sure
if that was still--

33:11.924 --> 33:14.099
\h\h\h\h\h\h-"Still"?
-Sorry, Dr. Bechley.

33:14.099 --> 33:15.759
Uh, I’m so sorry I’m late,

33:15.759 --> 33:18.594
and I was actually hoping
that I could make it up to you

33:18.594 --> 33:20.792
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hby helping out
with carving the turkey.

33:20.792 --> 33:22.132
Oh...

33:22.132 --> 33:23.594
\h\h\h\hI watched this
really fascinating

33:23.594 --> 33:24.594
online tutorial.

33:24.594 --> 33:25.594
It turns out,

33:25.594 --> 33:26.660
we’ve been carving it wrong

33:26.660 --> 33:27.660
all along.

33:27.660 --> 33:29.297
There’s a hack now.

33:29.297 --> 33:30.627
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hThere’s, like,
a hack for everything, right?

33:30.627 --> 33:32.198
I should have told this to you.

33:32.198 --> 33:33.726
Um, my dad is a little
sensitive about the carving.

33:33.726 --> 33:35.462
Ah, I don’t know if "sensitive"
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\his the word.

33:35.462 --> 33:37.033
It’s just that I happen to know

33:37.033 --> 33:39.462
a method of disarticulation
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hthat I learned

33:39.462 --> 33:41.957
in medical school
on human corpses.

33:41.957 --> 33:43.198
GENEVIEVE:
Leon, for God’s sake,

33:43.198 --> 33:44.957
let the young man carve
the turkey.

33:44.957 --> 33:46.693
\h\h\h\h-What’s the harm?
-I really don’t need to.

33:46.693 --> 33:48.495
-I just thought it’d be fun.
\h-CORNELIUS: You don’t come

33:48.495 --> 33:50.396
into another man’s home
\hand carve his turkey.

33:50.396 --> 33:51.891
It’s not his home.
It’s my home.

33:51.891 --> 33:53.561
And he’s a guest in it.

33:53.561 --> 33:55.561
Actually, I wouldn’t mind
\hseeing this turkey hack.

33:55.561 --> 33:57.495
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hYeah, I’m--
I’m a little curious myself.

33:57.495 --> 33:58.957
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hLEON:
It’s really amazing.

33:58.957 --> 34:00.726
\h\h\h\h\h\hI’m not welcome
in the clinic anymore

34:00.726 --> 34:05.495
that I founded, and now I can’t
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\heven carve the turkey.

34:05.495 --> 34:07.891
I really don’t care
\h\habout carving.

34:07.891 --> 34:10.825
\h\h\hIt’s really more
about the sides, right?

34:12.594 --> 34:14.264
For what it’s worth,

34:14.264 --> 34:16.429
I thought that article was
\h\h\hvery poorly written.

34:16.429 --> 34:18.264
-(knife clangs)
\h-Oh, my God.

34:18.264 --> 34:21.264
Yep, yep, yep, yep.
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOkay.

34:21.264 --> 34:23.000
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hJULIA:
Dad, where are you going?

34:23.000 --> 34:24.429
Just going for a walk
\h\h\h\hto clear my head.

34:24.429 --> 34:25.759
Please don’t leave.

34:25.759 --> 34:27.264
I need some air.

34:27.264 --> 34:29.858
Uh...

34:29.858 --> 34:31.462
Julia, I...

34:34.429 --> 34:36.594
(sighs)

34:47.033 --> 34:48.594
(man clears throat)

34:50.792 --> 34:52.264
You guys can say it’s terrible.

34:52.264 --> 34:53.297
\h\h\h\h\h\hJULIA:
It’s not terrible.

34:53.297 --> 34:56.594
It’s, um, dense.

34:56.594 --> 34:58.264
-Anyone like some water?
\h\h\h\h\h\h-GLADYS: Yes.

34:58.264 --> 35:00.033
\h\h\h\h\h-ISAAC: Please.
-DONOVAN: I’ll take some.

35:00.033 --> 35:02.099
This is your recipe, Gladys?

35:02.099 --> 35:04.066
It’s an interpretation.

35:04.066 --> 35:06.726
But you don’t need to be
a great cook to be a great mom.

35:06.726 --> 35:08.495
GENEVIEVE: I certainly
proved that in my day.

35:08.495 --> 35:10.627
-(cell phone chimes)
\h\h\h\h-(both laugh)

35:10.627 --> 35:11.726
What is it, babe?

35:11.726 --> 35:13.099
Oh, nothing.
It’s--it’s fine.

35:13.099 --> 35:15.264
Um, Cornelius,

35:15.264 --> 35:16.759
we almost forgot
about your Cognac.

35:16.759 --> 35:18.693
\h-TIM: Ah.
-Excuse me.

35:23.231 --> 35:25.528
I’ll help her with the glasses.

35:29.165 --> 35:32.099
(footsteps approaching,
\h\hindistinct chatter)

35:32.099 --> 35:34.924
Edie, you can’t hide
\h\h\hfrom your mother.

35:34.924 --> 35:36.759
What’s happening?

35:36.759 --> 35:38.429
(sighs)

35:38.429 --> 35:41.495
I chose him, Mom.
I love him.

35:41.495 --> 35:43.198
I’m trying.

35:43.198 --> 35:45.330
Well, trying is good,

35:45.330 --> 35:47.462
but pretending...

35:47.462 --> 35:48.792
I’m not pretending.

35:48.792 --> 35:51.198
I-I-I want to be
a good daughter-in-law.

35:51.198 --> 35:53.132
I want to be a good wife.

35:53.132 --> 35:54.825
<i>(solemn music)</i>

35:54.825 --> 35:56.759
But also...

35:56.759 --> 35:58.594
Also what?

35:58.594 --> 36:03.594
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:03.594 --> 36:05.858
Honey, is there somewhere
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hyou need to be?

36:05.858 --> 36:07.429
Someone you need to see?

36:07.429 --> 36:10.924
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:10.924 --> 36:12.264
-(glass shatters)
\h\h-(Edie gasps)

36:12.264 --> 36:14.891
\h\h\hOh, boy.
We’re okay.

36:14.891 --> 36:16.363
(chuckles)

36:16.363 --> 36:17.693
How clumsy of me.

36:17.693 --> 36:19.891
Cornelius is gonna be so upset

36:19.891 --> 36:21.957
unless you go right now
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hand replace it.

36:21.957 --> 36:24.297
I’ll stall.

36:24.297 --> 36:25.627
GENEVIEVE:
Go on.

36:25.627 --> 36:28.132
You don’t have all night.

36:28.132 --> 36:31.066
Ugh, Miss Butter Fingers here.

36:31.066 --> 36:34.396
Cornelius, I’m sorry.
I dropped the Cognac bottle.

36:34.396 --> 36:38.132
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:45.396 --> 36:47.000
-Hey.
-Hey.

36:47.000 --> 36:49.330
Hey, uh, I’m, uh--
I’m about to head out,

36:49.330 --> 36:51.231
but I brought you
\ha piece of pie.

36:51.231 --> 36:55.066
And I’m gonna warn you
this is truly terrible.

36:55.066 --> 36:56.759
It’s literally the texture
of a sofa cushion.

36:56.759 --> 36:58.099
(chuckles)

36:58.099 --> 37:00.099
Here.

37:00.099 --> 37:01.726
Thanks.

37:01.726 --> 37:03.231
(sighs)

37:03.231 --> 37:05.297
You doing okay?

37:10.000 --> 37:12.858
\h\h\h\h(whispering)
I’m embarrassed.

37:12.858 --> 37:14.594
I let that girl in here.

37:14.594 --> 37:16.264
That wasn’t your fault.

37:16.264 --> 37:18.495
Yeah, but she was right,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hyou know?

37:18.495 --> 37:19.891
All she had to do was like me,

37:19.891 --> 37:22.495
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hand I was eating
out of the palm of her hand.

37:23.957 --> 37:25.594
\h-That’s pathetic.
-It’s not pathetic.

37:25.594 --> 37:27.627
You’re vulnerable.

37:27.627 --> 37:29.033
There’s nothing wrong
with that.

37:29.033 --> 37:30.858
Except everybody keeps
\h\h\h\h\h\htalking about me

37:30.858 --> 37:31.924
like I’m defective.

37:31.924 --> 37:33.429
Hey, just because you have

37:33.429 --> 37:35.099
a drinking problem
doesn’t mean you’re defective.

37:35.099 --> 37:36.594
Hey, addiction is a disease
like everything else, right?

37:36.594 --> 37:39.429
You break your leg,
you go to a leg doctor.

37:39.429 --> 37:42.132
You break something in here...

37:42.132 --> 37:44.462
Roxy,
you have to deal with this.

37:44.462 --> 37:46.231
I mean, do you want me
to spell it out?

37:46.231 --> 37:47.858
Because I will.

37:49.858 --> 37:51.825
No, you’re right.

37:53.759 --> 37:55.891
<i>(soft music)</i>

37:55.891 --> 37:58.099
Thank you for not judging me.

37:58.099 --> 38:00.099
Of course.

38:00.099 --> 38:02.660
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hHey, um,
I could use some water.

38:02.660 --> 38:04.759
-Could you get me some?
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h-Yeah.

38:04.759 --> 38:06.924
You eat that, you’re definitely
gonna need some.

38:06.924 --> 38:08.957
\h\h\h\h\h-(chuckles)
-I’ll be right back.

38:08.957 --> 38:12.066
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:12.066 --> 38:14.231
(door closes)

38:14.231 --> 38:21.132
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:27.495 --> 38:28.924
(sniffles)

38:28.924 --> 38:35.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:40.858 --> 38:44.165
(sighs)

38:44.165 --> 38:46.000
Hey.

38:46.000 --> 38:48.264
I hope it’s okay that I’m here.

38:49.198 --> 38:51.033
What if I say it isn’t?

38:53.264 --> 38:56.330
I thought I made
the right decision,

38:56.330 --> 39:00.462
but it feels right to be here.

39:00.462 --> 39:02.858
And I understand
if you want to turn me away.

39:02.858 --> 39:05.198
I just...

39:05.198 --> 39:07.099
I just had to try.

39:09.858 --> 39:12.792
(sighs)

39:12.792 --> 39:15.792
<i>(dramatic music)</i>

39:15.792 --> 39:22.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:25.066 --> 39:27.132
-Edie!
\h-Hey.

39:27.132 --> 39:29.891
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:29.891 --> 39:31.627
\h\h\h\h\hLORENZO:
Come, we have pie.

39:31.627 --> 39:33.627
EDIE: Oh, wow.
\h\h\h\h\hOkay.

39:34.924 --> 39:37.429
\h\h-Oh, thank you.
-Thanks for coming.

39:37.429 --> 39:39.066
Oh, thank you for having us.

39:39.066 --> 39:41.264
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOh.
What about Edie?

39:41.264 --> 39:43.528
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAh, she texted, Mom.
She’s gonna meet us at home.

39:43.528 --> 39:44.660
\h\h\h\h\h-Bye.
-Thanks, Julia.

39:44.660 --> 39:47.396
Of course.
Happy Thanksgiving.

39:52.924 --> 39:54.495
DONOVAN: Thanks for letting me
charge this.

39:54.495 --> 39:57.594
Wow, no messages
from the kids, but--

39:57.594 --> 39:59.165
Oh, a voice mail from you.

39:59.165 --> 40:00.660
No, just delete that.

40:00.660 --> 40:02.165
No way.
I save all your messages.

40:02.165 --> 40:03.561
They have very high
replay value.

40:03.561 --> 40:04.660
Please don’t.

40:04.660 --> 40:06.264
<i>Hey, Donovan, it’s Julia.</i>

40:06.264 --> 40:07.792
<i>Uh, I was just calling to see</i>

40:07.792 --> 40:10.099
\h<i>\hhow you’re doing
and also--and I know</i>

40:10.099 --> 40:12.759
<i>this is weird--but if you were
</i>\h<i>\hhaving any second thoughts</i>

40:12.759 --> 40:14.132
<i>about coming tonight,
</i>\h\h\h\h\h<i>\hI just...</i>

40:14.132 --> 40:15.924
Did you disinvite me?

40:15.924 --> 40:18.594
Yes, I-I got scared

40:18.594 --> 40:21.429
\h\h\hthat my situation
would overwhelm you.

40:21.429 --> 40:24.099
Listen, your situation is,
you know, quite interesting.

40:24.099 --> 40:27.099
I’m not gonna lie,
but, hey, it’s not boring.

40:28.957 --> 40:32.594
I’m really sorry about my dad
\h\h\hand his whole turkey thing

40:32.594 --> 40:33.957
and him being so rude to you.

40:33.957 --> 40:35.759
And I just didn’t want
\h\h\h\h\h\hyou to come here

40:35.759 --> 40:38.264
and see how weird my family is
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hand run away,

40:38.264 --> 40:39.792
because I don’t want you
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hto run away.

40:39.792 --> 40:41.297
I don’t care about him.

40:41.297 --> 40:44.033
I care about you,
and I’m not running anywhere.

40:48.627 --> 40:50.462
\h\h\h\h\h\hSo no messages
from your kids, huh?

40:50.462 --> 40:52.660
\h\hSo I guess that means
you don’t have anywhere

40:52.660 --> 40:53.759
you need to be.

40:53.759 --> 40:55.264
I guess not.

40:55.264 --> 40:57.660
-That’s good.
\h-(chuckles)

41:00.462 --> 41:02.000
-What’s wrong?
\h-No, nothing.

41:02.000 --> 41:05.561
Just, um, I haven’t actually,

41:05.561 --> 41:08.099
um, slept with anyone
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hsince my wife.

41:08.099 --> 41:10.891
Sorry if that’s sad
\h\h\h\h\h\hand pathetic.

41:10.891 --> 41:13.792
No, it’s honest.

41:13.792 --> 41:15.825
And we don’t have to do
anything you’re not ready for.

41:15.825 --> 41:18.660
-Oh, I’m ready.
\h-(both laugh)

41:18.660 --> 41:20.759
Well, for what’s it worth,

41:20.759 --> 41:24.495
I haven’t been with anybody
I really cared about

41:24.495 --> 41:25.693
in a long time.

41:25.693 --> 41:28.495
So it’s kind of momentous
for me.

41:28.495 --> 41:31.495
<i>(bright piano music)</i>

41:31.495 --> 41:38.396
